%N A397477 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=0} binomial(2*k, k)/(2^(3*k)*(2*k+1)^3).
%H A397477 John M. Campbell, Paul Levrie, and Amrik Singh Nimbran, <a href="https://doi.org/10.7153/jca-2021-18-09">A natural companion to Catalan's constant</a>, Journal of Classical Analysis, Vol. 18, No. 2 (2021), pp. 117-135. See p. 121, eq. (19).
%H A397477 Steven R. Finch, <a href="https://compmath.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/central_binomial_coefficients_finch.pdf">Central Binomial Coefficients</a>, 2007. See p. 5.
%H A397477 Steven R. Finch, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2001.00578">Errata and Addenda to Mathematical Constants</a>, arXiv:2001.00578 [math.HO], 2020-2024. See section 1.22, p. 78.
%H A397477 Anthony Sofo and Amrik Singh Nimbran, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/10652469.2020.1765775">Euler-like sums via powers of log, arctan and arctanh functions</a>, Integral Transforms and Special Functions, Vol. 31, No. 12 (2020), pp. 966-981; <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Amrik-Nimbran/publication/341148394">ResearchGate link</a>. See Corollary 2.12.
%F A397477 Equals 4F3([1/2, 1/2, 1/2, 1/2], [3/2, 3/2, 3/2], 1/2), where 4F3 is a generalized hypergeometric function.
%F A397477 Equals (Pi^3/192 + Im(polylog(3, 1 + i)))/sqrt(2), where i is the imaginary unit (Finch, 2020).
%F A397477 Equals -sqrt(2)*L/2 + 23*sqrt(2)*Pi^3/768 + 3*sqrt(2)*Pi*log(2)^2/64, where L = Im(polylog(3, (i+1)/2)) (A355022) (Campbell et al., 2021).
%F A397477 Equals (log(2)*(8*G + Pi*log(2))/8 - A247508)/(2*sqrt(2)), where G is Catalan's constant (A006752).
%F A397477 3 formulas from Sofo and Nimbran (2020):
%F A397477 Equals (23*Pi^3/384 + 3*Pi*log(2)^2/32 - Sum_{k>=1} sin(Pi*k/4)/(2^(k/2)*k^3))/sqrt(2).
%F A397477 Equals (G*log(2)/2 + 5*Pi^3/96 + Pi*log(2)^2/16 - Sum_{k>=1} h'(2*k-1)/(2*(2*k-1)^2))/sqrt(2), where G is Catalan's constant (A006752), and h'(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} (-1)^(k+1)/(2*k-1).
%F A397477 Equals (23*Pi^3/384 + 3*Pi*log(2)^2/32 - Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k + 1)/4^k*(2/(4*k - 3)^3 + 2/(4*k - 2)^3 + 1/(4*k - 1)^3))/sqrt(2).
%e A397477 1.010154692526277592574269864638251385119930037754978...
%t A397477 RealDigits[(Pi^3/192 + Im[PolyLog[3, 1 + I]])/Sqrt[2], 10, 120][[1]]
%o A397477 (PARI) (Pi^3/192 + imag(polylog(3, 1 + I)))/sqrt(2)
%Y A397477 Sum_{k>=0} binomial(2*k, k)/(2^(3*k)*(2*k+1)^m): A002193 (m=0), A093954 (m=1), A263353 (m=2), this constant (m=3), A397478 (m=4).
%Y A397477 Cf. A000984, A002162, A006752, A247508, A355022.
